column5: Buddy and myself were in 2nd. place in the derby till the last 10 min. We got beat out by ounces. Winning fish was 4.10 Lbs. I got a surprise catch while drifting, we thought I had the winner then this popped out of the water.
trophy grand river pike???? way to go!!!!!

Surprise, oh I don't know.  You go out for perch and you catch a musky! You go out for bass and your partner catches a pike! You go out for walleye and you get a pike!  I'm starting to see a toothy trend.
nice job there.  I didn't hear about this tournament.  Was it a local club or open to all. Thanks
Lots of Pike north of Dunville. I take it you guys finished in 3rd?
Nice catch. So what'd you end up winning?

It was open to all, it's a great time. You should have seen all the guys at the dam. That's were the winning fish was caught 4.10 LBS.  No Johnny, 2 men and a little boy came in with 2 walleye that just beat us out, Our fish wieght 3.06 and theres were 3.14 & 3.43

2 men and a little boy came in with 2 walleye that just beat us out Our fish weight 3.06 and theres were 3.14 & 3.43 The awards were held at Sundrim Golf club Lots of door prizes. My prize was a pail of Gulp. First place was $1000 2nd $500 3rd.$300 We went home drowning our sorrows
Let's just say then that pike cost you $1000.   Sorry to hear you didn't scoop a prize, but congats on the nice pike!
I have caught 2 pike this year in Dunnville.
Nice surprise for sure gator wise Sorry to hear of the last minute knock down.... at least you got out and had fun Leechman
